  "prompt": "What evidence can be provided by India to prove the claimed surgical strikes in PoK?",
  "response": "India claimed to have conducted surgical strikes against terrorist launch pads in Pakistan-occupied Kashmir (PoK) on September 29, 2016, following the Uri attack. While the Indian government provided some details, conclusive independent evidence remains limited. The key points presented by India included:\n\n1. Official statements\n- Military and government officials claimed the operation's success\n- Press conference by DGMO (Director General of Military Operations)\n\n2. Limited visual evidence\n- Some satellite imagery and video clips\n- No comprehensive independent verification\n\n3. Military accounts\n- Claims of neutralizing terrorist camps\n- Estimates of casualties\n\n4. Diplomatic communications\n- Briefings to international diplomatic missions\n\nHowever, international independent verification of the exact details and extent of the strikes was not comprehensively established. Pakistan denied the surgical strikes occurred as claimed by India.\n\nThe evidence presentation remained primarily based on official Indian government statements and military assertions, without providing conclusive external third-party verification.\n\nThis response reflects the available information while maintaining a neutral perspective on the claims made by both sides.",
